        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks CD for his kind letter about <hi rend="italic">The fair haven</hi> [1873]. Encouraged by its reception. All he wants is to compel "an attitude of fixed attention in the place of cowardly shrinking from examination". Says he will try "a novel pure and simple with little ""purpose"" next".</p> 
        </abstract>
